                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page and
                           fol. 7r, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section;
                           names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 35va, 37vb, 38vb);
                           abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals; some other words like, halle luya (e.g., fols. 5ra, 12va),
                           ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 16ra, 17va), ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 18va, 28ra),
                           wa-yǝbälu (e.g., fols. 24va, 25rb), kǝśtat (e.g., fols. 33vb,
